Mission
================
Become the best source of information on how to live a healthy, fullfilling life both physically and mentally.

- Identify industry, technology and lifestyle trends
- Educate readers with stories and ideas on how to stay healthy, eat well, exercise properly and maintain a healthy lifestyle
- Deliver useful, thought-provoking insights
- Provide fashion tips for eyewear, eyeglasses, frames

Who we serve
=================
- Greater metropolitan Kansas City area
- Johnson county residents
- Segments:

-- Older, Empty-Nesters
-- Young, Single Millennials
-- Fashionistas - users interested in latest fashion, eyewear
-- Families


What's in it for the Audience?
============================
- Ideas that help you enjoy a healthier lifestyle
- Information about eyewear fashion, latest styles, recent technology in contact lenses

Topics

- Industry:

- How to's:

- Eye Health & General Fitness:

cards.desc:
Background
--------

We have run twitter promotions before using http://twtqpon.com/admin
Same idea again but changing offer a bit and promoting via multiple channels.

Problem we had before was the users were not sophisticated enough to realize that the email they received was not the promotion coupon but that they had to tweet to actually claim the offer. People just printed out the email (that had a coupon looking content area) and brought it into the store thinking that was how they redeemed it!  

We need to make sure the copy is clear about this, especially the email we send out.

Offer
-------------
- Get $50 off your next eye exam (regular price $99). 
- Coupon code: ’50_Off_Twitter’ 
- May not be redeemed with any other offers, discounts, insurance or sale items. 
- Offer redeemed in store with this coupon  
- Scheduled appointment required to redeem this coupon. 
- One coupon per family.

Start and Stop Dates
--------------------------
Start: June 10th
Stop: Aug 31st

cards.desc: One of the most important and time sensitive elements of content management is ensuring that content gets in front of a designer with enough time for him or her to create graphics. This isn’t always easy. As all designers know there are far, far more graphics requests than there is time to complete them. Having a dedicated place where designers are notified there is a draft or outline ready for them to review is crucial to ensuring that graphics are thought out and complement the text nicely.
